CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)
*CSS controls the appearance and layout of the webpage.
*Think of CSS as the design and styling of the skeleton.

  **example
    body {
    background-color: lightblue;
         }

    h1 {
    color: darkblue;
    text-align: center;
       }

    np {
    font-size: 18px;
       }

how html and css work together
    <head> <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"></head>




Key Differences
HTML                 	CSS
Structure          	Style
Content             Design
Elements	          Selectors & Properties
